Sentencas: Combining high-performance (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-delta (LSCF) cathodes with Y-doped ZrO2(YDZ) electrolytes in solid oxide fuel cells leads to the formation of SrZrO3 (SZO) as secondary phase with exceedingly low oxygen ion conductivity and poor catalytic capability.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: A promising prevention strategy is the insertion of Gd-doped CeO2 (GDC) as a reaction barrier.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: In this work, screen-printed GDC layers were sintered on YDZ substrates at temperatures varying from 1100 to 1400 degrees C. Subsequently, screen-printed LSCF was sintered on top at 1080 degrees C.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: The goal of this work was to understand microstructure formation during the two subsequent sintering processes by the analysis of nanometer-scale elemental distributions, crystal structures, and grain sizes of this extended cathode/electrolyte interface as a function of the GDC sintering temperature.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: Various representative regions on all samples were analyzed by transmission electron microscopy combined with energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy with high spatial resolution.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: For the lowest GDC sintering temperature an almost continuous ion-blocking SZO layer is formed during subsequent LSCF sintering.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: Although GDC densification does not occur, SZO formation is increasingly suppressed if higher GDC sintering temperatures are applied.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: This is attributed to a dense interdiffusion layer forming at the GDC/YDZ interface, which increases in thickness with GDC sintering temperature and contains a Zr-depleted region adjacent to the porous GDC layer.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: The dense and Zr-poor sublayer prevents the reaction of Sr species transported via gas phase during LSCF sintering with the Zr-rich YDZ substrate.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: The microstructural features have a pronounced influence on the electrical performance.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy measurements at open circuit voltage conditions reveal differences in the polarization resistance of up to 3 orders of magnitude.
Titulo: Gd0.2Ce0.8O2 Diffusion Barrier Layer between (La0.58Sr0.4)(Co0.2Fe0.8)O3-δ Cathode and Y0.16Zr0.84O2 Electrolyte for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells: Effect of Barrier Layer Sintering Temperature on Microstructure
